{"questionId":"26326","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cell is connected to an ideal voltmeter, a switch S and a resistor R. The resistance&nbsp;of R is 4.0 Ω.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/68cf21b2a5f6afc0f92b35b2f08c4fc9f6ca0aa6.png\"></p>\n<p>When S is open the reading on the voltmeter is 12 V. When S is closed the voltmeter&nbsp;reads 8.0 V.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the emf of the cell.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>12 V ✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"26326","referenceCode":"22M.2.HL.TZ2.4b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the emf of the cell.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.3 – Electric cells","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}